storyInfo: Skadi goes to the shore looking for food, but finds that in this part of the sea, there is nothing but monsters.

attributes.content: Look at you, even now irresolute, an ocean fish lost in its course.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: (She glances at him.)
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: You wish to know where I have brought you. You very much mind. You have not the qualification to take part in our congregation, yet your eyes tell me, you wish to know just what we will do to her.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Did you recover the kindred love between you? Could your heart be torn apart by what happened to your old relation? Do you feel it is unjust? Are you thus angered?
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: You are attempting to find what you cannot see.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: But of course. That is the expected response.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: You believe I wish to harm her. You are wrong. I wish to help her.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Only by elucidating where her—where all your pain lies at its source, can I better assist you in excising the problem point, is that not so?
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: As with you. You voluntarily became one of us, wishing to melt into the ocean true. Once you have completed this mission, your sordid nature will achieve purification. This is the ocean's charity to you.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: And in the end, charity alike will be extended to all your old relations. So long as they alike can relinquish their narrow views of a past enmity.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: To reunite you, that is the first step. To fathom you, that is the second step. And come the end, you will fathom us too.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: If you are able to reduce the nonsense by a measure, we may cooperate so much more harmoniously.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: I can also speak of things that will make you happy. Your old relation—the lucid one, she is already here.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Skadi?
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: She is not here.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: Naturally, she is not. Without my invitation, none may enter this place.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: She's entered the city. You know that.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: You have expressed surprise. That is very interesting. There is no sound in this city that I do not hear.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: And He admires all I do, has granted me the power, given my life further reach. My perception, my wit, all are no longer bound by the flesh you see before you.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: I am approaching perfection. I will accept your grudges.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: As for your old relation, now—her arrival was sooner than anticipated.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: 'Abyssal Hunters are bound by blood.'
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: She has no inkling of what awaits her. All you had to do was take the other away, and she has given chase here, not having once rested.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Truly a camaraderie to make one gasp. Does she know the state of you nowadays? What will she do when she confronts a traitor? Will she trust in your blood binding, old comrades rekindled, or will a blade pierce true through your body?
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: I have great expectations.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: (She turns to leave.)
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: You needn't hurry to find her. You've done very well. You have brought this one back to where she should remain, and led another into the city.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: He will be very pleased.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: He?
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: You need not know.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: We simply wait now. We wait until the time comes, and naturally, you may find your old relation then, and pass on to her our invitation.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: She is not sure to come.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: She will come. She will come seeking me herself.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: You're back again!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: We live in the best building in the whole north area. Look, this door still closes. A door that shuts closed is one of your best friends on a rainy day.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: People are nearby. Two of them.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: They're, well, they're usually here.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: One-hundred-and-thirty, one-hundred-and-thirty-one, one-hundred-and-thirty-two...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant

attributes.content: Hi, Brick, are you doing good today?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: One, two, three...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant

attributes.content: I'm sorry!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Poor guy, now he has to start over again. He's always sitting here, counting all the bricks in the street. Don't tell him I said, but each day's count isn't much like the last.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: And also, that one's Stonecolumn. He likes making his way all around the street pillars. When it's all dark and rainy he doesn't come out. He's a little old, and his legs start hurting when he gets wet.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You can just ignore them, and they'll ignore you too, just like they ignore me.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Come in, singer. Let me give you an official introduction. In here is my home.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Hi, Sheetmetal. Hi, Drywall. You're awake!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: (Strokes case)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ouch...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Hey, Woodframe. You brought this outside person into the house again.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: She's not bad.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She's from the outside.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Bench has taken a decent liking to her, haven't you, Bench?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Wgh... aogh...
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: Don't—Don't bite! You're going to chew the singer's skirt apart!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: *cough*.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: ...Not that it'll come apart.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It's all slobbery again. That's not very pretty.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Aogh, au-auwgh...
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: This rascal really has taken a shining to you, singer.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You see? Bench wants her to stay too.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You are scheming something. Do not think, I do not know.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Er...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: This will not, end well.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I'm not, okay, I don't have any plans at all.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What is the phrase...? Suit yourself.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: The rules, may not be broken.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Whether by you, or by her.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I will be watching.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: We shall go.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Phew... they finally left.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer, don't be afraid. This is just the kind of person Sheetmetal is. He may seem very frightful, but he won't really do anything to us.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Okay, I know you're not afraid. Since you're so much more powerful than them.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I just wanted to say, if he really tried something—*snort*—I wouldn't be scared of him either.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: *Sigh*.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You're sighing.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: This barrel's empty. So is the tray.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Let me just think... maybe there's still some food under the bed.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Is this the bed?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It is. Does it seem very odd? Were the beds in your home not metal?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I don't mind too much.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You can find wooden beds in some houses, too. Wood's surprisingly useful. Wood can burn, and make houses brighter and warmer at once. There are some times if you fall ill here when the winters won't be kind to you.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Eh-heh—look, this is my treasure box. I filled it a touch full when I woke up this morning.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Help me for a moment here, get this dry seagrass out of my sight. No, don't throw it on the floor. Even if we can't eat it, we can still pad out the bed with it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You have a lot.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That's right. I hide everything useful inside here.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Take a look at this, they're clothes I'm sewing right now. I sharpened up a shell into a needle recently, and it's so much better to use than all those years-old ones.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'm fairly short of material. Still need to go searching properly through the city south. Maybe there'll be some buried so deep that nobody's taken it yet.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It'll be getting cold soon, so I need to hurry up.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: No, don't you dare, Bench, you can't touch these clothes! These are for Grandma Petra. Her cough just keeps getting worse.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Not this either! You let go!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Woodframe.
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: I've told you how many times? It's not Woodframe, it's Pictureframe!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Also, you can't even eat this! There's no point in you even having it!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Woodframe... Pictureframe?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You heard them calling me that?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I only know you as Anita.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I picked Anita for myself... I heard it in one of Grandma Petra's stories. She was a girl just like you, she could really sing. It sounds much nicer than Woodframe, doesn't it?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Most of us here have no names. Whatever came to mind first is what we use. Brick's always counting bricks, Sheetmetal has a sheetmetal fence running all around his house.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: They call me Woodframe. Because underneath this pictureframe is where Grandma Petra found me.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You mentioned your own mother before.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She didn't give me up to anyone else. Brave, she was. When I was born, there were no children here. Children couldn't survive.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Those years, nobody dared go against Grandma Petra... she gave me a share of food. Don't let her poor health now fool you, she's this city's most fearsome person by far.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Even Sheetmetal fears her.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Things are much better now. That priest taught us how to survive. Just look at Bench, and those children over there. I believe in this place of ours becoming a lively one someday.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Aaah... ah...
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: So long as you don't keep taking what's mine. You're a good kid still, aren't you, Bench?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It doesn't matter if anything else gets taken away. Every night when I go to sleep, I hide this box away. They wouldn't know how to find it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Ugh, we don't really go 'yours' or 'mine' here. I understand hiding things is bad. Singer, you won't go telling anyone else, will you? You're not interested in my things to boot.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Do you trust in me?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You're a guest. Grandma Petra taught me that we should properly receive guests.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: There it is, I knew it was there. Look, there's still one fin left.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: This odor...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It's half a month old. Still quite fresh as fish go.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Pull it apart, and this half... is for Bench. Here, Bench, food for you here!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Ah... aaah... (He swallows it.)
attributes.name: Young Inhabitant

attributes.content: Alright, and this half is for you. Leave the bones when you're done eating. I can boil some soup with them after.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I can go to find food too.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: But the day still hasn't come! If you went out now, you probably couldn't find anything to eat.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Can't say until you try.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She talks, and suddenly she's gone. Seriously, how odd she is!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.text: The wandering singer in the red dress, carrying her tremendous case on her back, strolls casually through the street.
Still no one heeds her. In a street still and ashen, naught moves but a flutter of red.

attributes.content: Still following.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.text: Skadi suddenly picks up in speed.
The indistinct shadow sweeps through the way, in the manner of a wave driven on by a gale.
It is as if she is about to charge headlong into the ocean—and then comes to a sudden halt.

The singer in the red dress clutches her harp to her chest, using one hand to clamber a nomadic city's wreckage, her vision sweeping past the chapel towering on the high cliff, resting on the pitch-black sea surface.
From a crag hanging over ten meters high, she leaps down.

attributes.content: The shore. She has gone to the shore.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Yes, Sheetmetal, your thinking is correct. She wants to enter the sea. She intends to set into it.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: The time, is not yet come.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: The priest spoke so. The tide must flood and ebb one-hundred times, before we are permitted, to enter the sea.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sheetmetal, we cannot come here. The shore, does not permit us to.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: That is meaningless. We will, block her.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Block her? As if we could defeat her?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: The priest spoke, we must wait one hundred times, before we may go. It is only, the ninety-ninth time now.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: She will obtain nothing at all. The shore today, has nothing at all.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: So what is she looking for?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sheetmetal, it is bitterly cold here, I am hungry, we cannot come here, and you should not ask.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Is there anything in the sea?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I do not know.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Even if you knew, what then?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I do not know. Sheetmetal, what you say, I do not know any of. I do not understand.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Where is the furthest we have traveled, in the past?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: The westernmost of the west. A long time ago. In those days, we were, no taller than this. We could still, collect food in the town.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Borderline. We do not often, say this word. We have seen, this city's, edge.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: That was you, Sheetmetal, not we.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: At that time, I was dizzy with hunger.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You said, you wanted to go further still. You wanted, to push your luck.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: It was to try my luck.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Hmph. You never could, make any sense. The priest gave you such years of teaching. You never could learn.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Heh-heh, Sheetmetal, you make. Sense of me.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You said so, at that time too.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: You have always trusted me. You let me take the can you kept. I traveled another day.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: And then you came back.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Yes, I came back.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: You ate nothing, for several days after. I thought, you wanted to starve yourself to death.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: I thought of it. But what meaning, would starving myself have?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: After all, we will all perish come not too long.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: You are giving me a shock. You said this back then too. I do not know what you are talking about.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Afterward... the priest came. It was only when he came, that I felt a change. We all changed.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: The priest, has a good life. He says we can have one. What he says is true.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: It is true. Because... it is the truth. He let us see it.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Because of the priest, I survived. We all survived. That is, very good.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: That line, no one can cross.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Is that line, the seawater line?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: All lines. Just like the traps Woodframe makes. They stop, even outsiders.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: We cannot exit either. That is for the best.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sheetmetal... your leg, is going to meet the water!
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Water... yes. I shall not cross.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Even if I crossed over... crossed over, there may well be nothing there at all.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Phew... Sheetmetal, you finally stopped walking. You scared me just now.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Do not be like that, asking so many questions. You are like Woodframe, when you always ask. She was always strange. The priest said too that something is wrong about her, did he not?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Questioning... cannot help us.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Only answers have any meaning.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: You impress me so, Sheetmetal. You are the only one who remembers, the priest's words as strongly.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Look, she has not stopped walking along the shore.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sheetmetal, where are you going? Are you going to follow too? No, that is not right, we may not, and cannot follow her!
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Even I know, we cannot defeat her. We have no way to drive her out.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: She cannot return now.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: That... That is a very good thing for us.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: I want the big case she has. There is surely much to eat inside.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: The case is not here. She took it.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: There is only this... this, she placed it on the rocks. I do not know what this is.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: She is always holding it. It should be something good, no?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: May I... May I try a bite, Sheetmetal? I am so very hungry.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: (Plink-plunk)
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: What—What is this? I have never heard a sound like this before.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: (Plink-plunk, plink-plunk)
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Stop it quickly, Sheetmetal, this sound is making my stomach and teeth shake without end. If you are fond of holding it then hold it. I am going back after all.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: No meaning. This also has no meaning.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: This useless thing. It should be left on the ground. To rot.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: The whole way, I thought it was somebody else following me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You—You returned! How were you able? Nobody who goes to, the shore at this time, will return.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You want to enter the sea.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: I'm just taking a walk around the area.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Is there anything in the sea?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: There's nothing at all.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: That cannot be.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: You have turned stranger and stranger, Sheetmetal. You are still asking these questions I do not understand. Did we not come here to block her?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Now she is heading back. We may go back.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: You saw it. You know.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Sheetmetal, you are shaking. Have you become ill?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Don't come near.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And what if I do? Will you beat us so we are lying on the floor, like before?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: There is something in the sea, correct?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Don't move.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Aaaaagh—
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Drywall!
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: This stone... her movements, are truly fast.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Was that a sound from my mouth? Sheetmetal, I made a sound. My heart is beating wild. Have I become ill too?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: I believe, your head will explode with a bang. Just like a shell smashed open, there will be something shining bright white inside.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Will I die then?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: We will know the next time we try. What has fallen apart now is something else. I have never seen a thing like this before.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Why can it... still move?!
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant A

attributes.content: Run. Head back to the city. Quickly.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: —Remember to leave my harp here.
attributes.name: Skadi
